put forward for a Palestinian

14:58.700 --> 15:00.800 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
state by 2005.

15:00.800 --> 15:02.833 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That was over a decade ago.

15:02.833 --> 15:07.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, the question is, if we are
against the continued settlement
activity and for a two-state

15:07.133 --> 15:12.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
solution, why are we going
to continue with the status
quo, on which we see trends on

15:14.100 --> 15:16.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
both sides, Israeli
and Palestinian trends,
that are putting peace
farther and farther

15:16.833 --> 15:18.900 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
away?

15:18.900 --> 15:21.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: You say it's
bipartisan, but as you
very well know, the
leadership -- Republican

15:21.033 --> 15:26.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
leadership in the Congress is
raining down now with criticism,
the incoming Democratic

15:28.433 --> 15:33.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
leader in the Senate, Senator
Schumer from New York, is
criticizing this decision.

15:35.433 --> 15:39.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It sounds like the
administration is, if
not alone, certainly is
in the minority on this

15:41.633 --> 15:43.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
position today.

15:43.600 --> 15:48.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
RHODES: Well, look, we respect,
of course, friends on both
sides of the aisle who have

15:50.433 --> 15:52.533 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
expressed different
views on this.

15:52.533 --> 15:57.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Again, I think the question is
going to be when history looks
at these types of decisions,

15:59.633 --> 16:02.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
when people look back and
they say, you saw tens of
thousands of settlements
being constructed,

16:04.833 --> 16:08.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
you saw as was addressed in
the resolution, incitement to
violence on the Palestinian

16:08.633 --> 16:10.700 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
side.

16:10.700 --> 16:14.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The question is, do we not have
responsibility to lay down a
marker here about what we think

16:15.367 --> 16:17.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
is actual U.S. policy?

16:17.500 --> 16:20.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have a resolution like this
that is entirely consistent with
the policy, how can we continue

16:20.900 --> 16:22.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to veto that over
and over again?

16:22.900 --> 16:26.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Finally, are you
comfortable -- is the president
comfortable with this knowing

16:26.233 --> 16:31.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
