weapons, and Joseph
Cirincione, the president
of the Ploughshares

17:53.000 --> 17:56.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Fund, a non-profit organization
that advocates for disarmament.

17:56.533 --> 17:58.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
He, too, has written
widely on the subject.

17:58.867 --> 18:01.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Gentlemen, thank you both
for joining us tonight.

18:01.233 --> 18:06.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Mr. Cirincione, let me start
with you, when you hear or
read the president-elect saying

18:08.200 --> 18:12.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that the United States must
greatly strengthen and expand
its nuclear capability and then

18:14.567 --> 18:17.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
tell Mika Brzezinski this
morning, "Let it be an arms
race," what's your reaction?

18:17.200 --> 18:19.067 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JOSEPH CIRINCIONE,
PLOUGHSHARES FUND: Stunned.

18:19.067 --> 18:23.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
An ill-considered,
disrespectful and dangerous
series of statements.

18:23.267 --> 18:28.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This would upend decades of
Republican and Democratic policy
that ever since Ronald Reagan

18:30.200 --> 18:34.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has been reducing nuclear
arsenals, both in the United
States and Russia and around the

18:34.900 --> 18:37.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
world, stopping other countries
from getting nuclear weapons.

18:37.833 --> 18:42.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
By using that word
"expand", he says he wants
to grow the arsenal or
grow the capabilities.

18:44.233 --> 18:47.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Look, nobody is against keeping
a strong nuclear deterrent.

18:47.033 --> 18:49.967 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
If that's all he said, we
wouldn't be having this debate.

18:49.967 --> 18:54.967 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
President Obama has put
in train a trillion-dollar
program to replace every
single nuclear weapon

18:56.467 --> 18:58.667 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
we have over the next 25 years.

18:58.667 --> 19:01.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Donald Trump seems to be saying
he wants to go ahead with this.

19:01.800 --> 19:06.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His advisors tried to walk it
back, but he himself said this
morning, let it be an arms

19:07.767 --> 19:09.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
race.

19:09.833 --> 19:12.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is an extremely dangerous
posture, that's why people
all over the globe are worried

19:12.900 --> 19:14.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
and talking about this today.

19:14.433 --> 19:16.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
YANG: Matthew Kroenig,
what's your take?

19:16.467 --> 19:18.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MATTHEW KROENIG, GEORGETOWN
UNIVERSITY: Well, the statement
is certainly controversial but

19:18.567 --> 19:21.067 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
I think Trump is
basically right.

19:21.067 --> 19:25.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
U.S. nuclear policy in
the U.S. can't be static,
it has to respond to
international politics

19:28.367 --> 19:31.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and all America's nuclear
armed rivals, Russia,
China, North Korea, are
expanding and modernizing

19:31.733 --> 19:34.367 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
their arsenals.

19:34.367 --> 19:36.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, it doesn't make sense
for the United States
to continue reducing its
arsenal as our adversaries

19:36.767 --> 19:39.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
are going in the
other directions.

19:39.200 --> 19:42.733 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And moreover, many of
these countries, especially
Russia, are relying
more not less on nuclear

19:42.733 --> 19:44.667 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
weapons in their strategy.

19:44.667 --> 19:48.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, again, the United States
needs to take that into account
as it formulates its own

19:48.233 --> 19:50.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
nuclear posture.

19:50.333 --> 19:53.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And so, I think some
strengthening of U.S.
nuclear strategy and
U.S. nuclear posture

19:53.367 --> 19:55.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
has been long overdue.

19:55.367 --> 19:59.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
YANG: Matthew Kroenig, when you
say the United States shouldn't
be reducing its arsenal,

20:01.600 --> 20:04.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
