both countries can
have 1,550 deployed
strategic nuclear weapons.

20:16.033 --> 20:18.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Right now, the United States
is actually well under
200 or so warheads under.

20:18.633 --> 20:21.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
The Russians are
250 warheads above.

20:21.267 --> 20:25.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, there is a gap of
about 400 warheads that's
worrying in and of itself,
and it raises questions

20:27.900 --> 20:30.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
about Russia -- whether
Russia actually intends
to follow through on
this agreement or not.

20:30.933 --> 20:34.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, this is one of the measures
that a new president can
take to strengthen America's

20:34.267 --> 20:37.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
