the size of the arsenal, at
least to the limits allowed for

20:37.767 --> 20:38.767 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
under new START.

20:38.767 --> 20:40.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
YANG: You're shaking your head.

20:40.233 --> 20:42.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
CIRINCIONE: Well, that's because
he's playing with numbers.

20:42.833 --> 20:46.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Yes, it's true, we both
have about 7,000 warheads
in our total inventory
and the ones that the

20:48.533 --> 20:52.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
treaty counts, you know,
we're a couple hundred under.

20:52.133 --> 20:55.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But we have more
launchers, more missiles,
more delivery vehicles.

20:55.033 --> 20:57.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
We're a couple hundred over
where the Russians are.

20:57.800 --> 21:00.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But at these levels, those
numbers don't matter.

21:00.633 --> 21:04.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We both have enough
weapons to destroy the
world several times over.

21:04.600 --> 21:06.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We don't need to expand this.

21:06.633 --> 21:11.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And here's the real problem,
when the two big guys, the
people with 95 percent of the

21:13.267 --> 21:16.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
