Russia together have 95 percent
of all the weapons in the

21:16.467 --> 21:19.967 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
world, when we say we need
more, what is China to think?

21:19.967 --> 21:21.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
They have about 200.

21:21.100 --> 21:22.767 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Do they start building more?

21:22.767 --> 21:24.767 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
How about India and Pakistan?

21:24.767 --> 21:29.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
And that's the big worry
that you have here is
this ill-considered
tweet could launch

21:29.500 --> 21:31.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
a global arms race.

21:31.433 --> 21:35.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Twitter is fine for criticizing
Alec Baldwin, but don't
use it to make U.S. policy.

21:36.767 --> 21:37.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Mr. Trump, step away
from the Twitter.

21:37.733 --> 21:39.067 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
YANG: Go ahead.

21:39.067 --> 21:41.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KROENIG: Three thoughts on that.

21:41.200 --> 21:44.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One, there's a 400 warhead
difference, I do disagree,
I do think that matters.

21:44.800 --> 21:48.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And even if we don't think it
matters, the Russians pay close
attention to nuclear weapons.

21:48.900 --> 21:50.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They rely more on nuclear
weapons in their strategy.

21:50.933 --> 21:55.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so, I think they think this
difference matters and they
say, see, this U.S. failure

21:57.167 --> 21:59.667 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to respond to some of their
actions as sign of weakness.

21:59.667 --> 22:03.200 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And in terms of this
idea that if we reduce
our arsenal, somehow
China and other countries

22:03.200 --> 22:07.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
are going to come along,
that was the position
that really underline
the Obama administration

22:07.267 --> 22:11.867 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
nuclear strategy and
we've seen that it hasn't
worked, as the United
States reduced its arsenal,

22:11.867 --> 22:14.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
other countries have gone
in the other directions.

22:14.233 --> 22:16.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, I don't see this
as the United States
starting an arms race.

22:16.967 --> 22:20.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Quite the contrary, it's really
responding to what's going
on in these other countries.

22:20.500 --> 22:23.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
And I think a failure
to respond is what would
be really dangerous.

22:23.600 --> 22:25.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I think it would incentivize
further nuclear aggression.

