goes ahead and builds
a whole new fleet of
ballistic missile submarines

22:50.833 --> 22:55.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in the next decade, it has
to cut its conventional
navy by 50 percent.

22:57.300 --> 22:59.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Who would make that
kind of choice?

22:59.367 --> 23:02.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, these are some of the
considerations that will
face the new administration.

23:02.700 --> 23:07.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And here's the upside of this
-- let's say this is all about
negotiating leverage, this

23:09.733 --> 23:12.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is Mr. Trump opening up closed
issues, looking for bargaining
in ahead of his meeting with

23:12.533 --> 23:15.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Vladimir Putin, which
will probably occur in the
beginning of next year.

23:15.900 --> 23:20.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Well, here's where he could cash
in, he should take a page from
Ronald Reagan, and negotiate

23:20.200 --> 23:25.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
with Putin, deep cuts in both
sides' nuclear forces, get rid
of these unnecessary weapons

23:27.200 --> 23:30.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we don't need, save hundreds
of billions of dollars to use
for conventional forces, and

23:31.567 --> 23:32.800 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
really make a name for himself.

23:32.800 --> 23:35.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This could be the
deal of a lifetime.

23:35.000 --> 23:38.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This would put him in the
history books and then we won't
be talking about these silly

23:38.433 --> 23:39.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
tweets.

23:39.600 --> 23:41.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
YANG: Matthew Kroenig,
what about that?

23:41.600 --> 23:46.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's a dealmaker, he's
businessman and he talks about
trying to keep his negotiating

23:47.500 --> 23:49.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
opponents off balance
and that sort of thing.

23:49.700 --> 23:54.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Can we learn anything or take
anything from this about what
kind of foreign policy President

23:55.333 --> 23:56.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Trump will be?

23:56.300 --> 23:57.567 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
KROENIG: Well, two points.

23:57.567 --> 23:59.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
First to Joe, first
on the modernization.

23:59.600 --> 24:02.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Joe has thought a lot about
these issues, but he is
outside the mainstream.

24:02.967 --> 24:06.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There is a bipartisan consensus
that the United States needs
to modernize the arsenal.

24:06.900 --> 24:08.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
This was Obama
administration's policy.

24:08.800 --> 24:12.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It has support from
Republicans and that should
go ahead under Trump.

24:12.367 --> 24:14.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Joe also raised
the issue of cost.

24:14.867 --> 24:18.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But the cost of these
modernization programs,
you mentioned $1 trillion
over 30 years, but

24:18.933 --> 24:22.300 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
that comes to about 5 percent
of the U.S. defense budget.

24:22.300 --> 24:27.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, current Secretary of Defense
Ash Carter has said this is
the bedrock of our security.

24:29.333 --> 24:30.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Former Secretary of Defense
Chuck Hagel has said it's the
most important mission of the

24:30.867 --> 24:32.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Department of Defense.

24:32.900 --> 24:35.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I don't think anybody
thinks 5 percent is too much
for the most important mission

24:35.667 --> 24:37.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
of the Department of Defense.

24:37.333 --> 24:41.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
On your question, what
does this signal about
Trump's foreign policy?

24:41.133 --> 24:45.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It's difficult to know
whether this means a change in
U.S. nuclear policy or not.

24:45.000 --> 24:48.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All we have to go on is a
tweet and a couple of tweets
and a couple of statements.

24:48.400 --> 24:51.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It may mean just continuing
Obama's policy of modernization.

24:51.467 --> 24:54.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
But I am hopeful that
it means strengthening
the arsenal because I
do think there are some

24:54.900 --> 24:58.800 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
things the United
States can do within its
international obligations
to strengthen deterrence.

24:58.800 --> 25:00.467 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
YANG: I'm sorry, I'm afraid
we have to leave there.

25:00.467 --> 25:05.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Matthew Kroenig
and Joe Cirincione,
thanks for joining us.

25:09.200 --> 25:13.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
CIRINCIONE: Thank you.

