25:16.233 --> 25:21.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: Next, a long
looked-for breakthrough
in the battle against
the deadly Ebola virus.

25:23.733 --> 25:28.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
One experimental vaccine
has been shown to be 100
percent effective on humans.

25:29.600 --> 25:30.467 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Hari Sreenivasan has the story.

25:30.467 --> 25:32.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
(BEGIN VIDEOTAPE)

25:32.567 --> 25:34.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN, PBS NEWSHOUR
CORRESPONDENT: The results of
a two-year trial led by the

25:34.567 --> 25:37.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
World Health Organization
were published in the
journal "Lancet" yesterday.

25:37.633 --> 25:42.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They showed that of nearly 6,000
people vaccinated in Guinea last
year, none had contracted Ebola

25:44.033 --> 25:45.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
after a ten-day period.

25:45.733 --> 25:49.567 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
While in the group not
vaccinated, 23 cases developed.

25:49.567 --> 25:54.567 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The vaccine still needs
regulatory approval,
but is considered so
effective that some 300,000

25:55.733 --> 25:57.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
doses have already
been stockpiled.

25:57.567 --> 26:02.567 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
The 2014 Ebola epidemic in West
Africa killed 11,000 people.

26:04.533 --> 26:06.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For more on this promising
news, we turn once again
to Dr. Anthony Fauci.

26:06.700 --> 26:10.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
He's director of the
National Institute for
Allergy and Infectious
Diseases, and has long

26:10.733 --> 26:12.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
been involved in
vaccine development.

26:12.767 --> 26:17.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Dr. Fauci, everyone's
pretty excited about the
100 percent efficacy rate.

26:17.233 --> 26:19.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Let's look under the hood a bit.

26:19.333 --> 26:23.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This isn't the same type of
clinical trial that we're used
to in drug approval or vaccine

26:23.100 --> 26:24.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
approval, is it?

26:24.100 --> 26:26.233 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
DR.

26:26.233 --> 26:28.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
ANTHONY FAUCI, NATIONAL
INSTITUTE OF ALLERGY
AND INFECTIOUS DISEASE:
No, it's a bit unusual.

26:28.267 --> 26:31.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The vaccine trial is referred
to as a ring vaccine trial
which means that cases were

26:32.633 --> 26:36.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
identified in Guinea
that indeed had Ebola.

26:36.033 --> 26:41.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Then, instead of preemptively
ahead of time vaccinating whole
groups of populations, the

26:43.000 --> 26:47.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
individuals were divided into
two separate groups, groups
that were vaccinated immediately

26:49.467 --> 26:53.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
who had contact with the index
case or cases or contact of
contacts, and another group

26:55.900 --> 26:58.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that was vaccinated
21 days later.

26:58.933 --> 27:03.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it was more of an acute
response to an outbreak by
trying to protect those people

27:05.600 --> 27:10.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
who were, in reality
or potentially exposed
to the index cases.

27:12.067 --> 27:15.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's not the standard way
that you do a vaccine trial.

27:15.900 --> 27:20.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so, although these results
are really quite encouraging,
there is still a lot more

27:20.800 --> 27:25.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
work to be done on vaccines
for Ebola, and that's exactly
where we're heading with this,

27:27.800 --> 27:31.267 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
to get many more people
in a larger trial and
to also determine, is
the effect durable?

27:33.233 --> 27:36.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
In other words, if I vaccinate
you now, will you be protected
six months, eight months

27:38.433 --> 27:42.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
or a year from now and
just how powerful that
protective response would be.

27:44.133 --> 27:48.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's really the kinds of
questions that still remain a
bit unanswered, despite the

27:48.033 --> 27:52.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
fact that this finding now
from the Guinea trial is
really quite impressive.

27:52.767 --> 27:56.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: There was one
vaccine that was tested at the
center of this, but there are

27:56.400 --> 27:58.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
multiple strains of Ebola.

27:58.533 --> 28:02.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
FAUCI: That's another question
that needs to be answered
and it's a good point that

28:02.533 --> 28:04.567 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
you bring up.

28:04.567 --> 28:08.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This vaccine that was
tested in Guinea against
the Zaire strain of Ebola.

28:11.733 --> 28:15.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There are more than one strain,
particularly, a second train
called the Sudan strain, but

28:15.933 --> 28:18.467 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
maybe two other strains.

28:18.467 --> 28:23.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And when we ultimately
get the vaccine that
what we would consider
to be the optimal season,

28:25.533 --> 28:28.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
we would want one that, A, has
a great durability of effect,
that would be effective over a

28:30.533 --> 28:33.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
considerable period of time,
and, B, something that would
be able to protect essentially

28:35.733 --> 28:39.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
against all strains of Ebola,
because there are different
strains that pop up in different

28:41.600 --> 28:44.567 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
parts of sub-Saharan Africa,
and we have clear-cut
experience with that.

28:44.567 --> 28:48.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SREENIVASAN: So, given the
test that's just been done with
this specific vaccine, this

28:48.033 --> 28:51.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is not like a polio vaccine
where you get it once in your
life and you're vaccinated.

28:51.967 --> 28:56.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You're still going to need a
lot more tests to figure out
that combination of different

28:57.833 --> 28:59.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
viruses and how long they last.

28:59.433 --> 29:00.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
FAUCI: Absolutely.

29:00.667 --> 29:03.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Those are critical
questions that you ask.

29:03.500 --> 29:08.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This -- some people when they
hear about how really impressive
the results are, they think,

29:08.400 --> 29:12.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
OK, we're done now with the
Ebola vaccine, we're going to
move on because we've solved

29:12.933 --> 29:15.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the problem.

29:15.033 --> 29:18.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We haven't come anywhere
near solving the problem
because there are still
so many unanswered

29:18.300 --> 29:23.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
questions that we need to pursue
before we get a vaccine that
we feel would be universally

29:25.733 --> 29:30.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
able to be widespread
administered to people
to protect them from
outbreaks of Ebola of

29:31.600 --> 29:32.600 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
multiple different strains.

29:32.600 --> 29:33.867 align:left position:25%,start line:86.67% size:75%
There's a lot of
work to be done.

29:33.867 --> 29:35.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SREENIVASAN: All right.

29:35.867 --> 29:38.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
While we have you, I also
wanted to just ask you about the
avian flu that's in Asia right

29:38.900 --> 29:40.967 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
now.

29:40.967 --> 29:43.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We're reporting about the
millions of birds in Korea and
other parts of Asia that have

29:43.000 --> 29:44.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
been culled already.

29:44.900 --> 29:46.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
How concerned should
we about this?

29:46.933 --> 29:49.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
FAUCI: We need to pay
attention to this.

29:49.067 --> 29:53.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I don't think there's any real
need to panic at all about it,
because we have been following

29:53.133 --> 29:58.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
outbreaks of bird
flu for decades.

30:00.100 --> 30:03.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The first time we got involved
with it here was back in the
'90s in Hong Kong when you

30:03.533 --> 30:08.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
had the H5N1 which are viruses
that are influenza viruses that
are fundamentally viruses of

30:11.067 --> 30:16.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
fowl, water fowl, or
chickens, sometimes
pigs and other animals.

30:18.067 --> 30:21.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
They rarely jump into species
and infect humans, and when they
do infect humans, they do not

30:23.067 --> 30:25.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
efficiently spread
from human-to-human.

30:25.733 --> 30:29.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's where most of the bird
flu situation is right now.

30:29.833 --> 30:34.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But having said that, we
always have to be alert for the
threat or the possibility that

30:36.800 --> 30:40.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
they may, when they jump species
like from a chicken or another
type of a fowl to a human,

30:41.933 --> 30:45.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that they then become really
efficient in spreading
from person to person.

30:45.533 --> 30:47.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We've not seen that thus far.

30:47.700 --> 30:52.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hopefully, we'll never see it,
but we've even begun trying to
develop vaccines against some

30:54.067 --> 30:56.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
of these avian type flu.

30:56.367 --> 30:59.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, no need to panic but
don't just blow it off.

30:59.667 --> 31:01.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
We've got to keep
our eye out on it.

31:01.433 --> 31:02.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
SREENIVASAN: All right.

31:02.667 --> 31:06.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Dr. Anthony Fauci,
thanks so much.

31:06.033 --> 31:10.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
FAUCI: Good to be with you.

