UNIDENTIFIED MALE (through
translator): We came
here looking for life.

32:41.233 --> 32:46.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GUERRERO: He said he spent a lot
of money to make it this far,
as did his fellow travelers.

32:48.233 --> 32:51.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The journey involved long
walking stretches, bus travel
and more through some of Latin

32:51.367 --> 32:53.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
America's most
dangerous countries.

32:53.333 --> 32:56.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
UNIDENTIFIED MALE (through
translator): I saw
many, many people die.

32:56.500 --> 33:00.367 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
GUERRERO: That's why
sudden shifts in U.S.
immigration policy have
left him so bewildered.

33:00.367 --> 33:05.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Since the 2010 earthquake, the
U.S. has been letting Haitians
in under a humanitarian parole

33:06.267 --> 33:08.367 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
provision.

33:08.367 --> 33:12.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But a few weeks ago, responding
to the overwhelming influx of
migrants, the U.S. revokes that

33:13.133 --> 33:15.133 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
privilege.

33:15.133 --> 33:19.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The decision to resume
deportations was motivated by
improved conditions in Haiti.

33:21.100 --> 33:24.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But Hurricane Matthew struck
a few days later, plunging
the country back into crisis.

33:26.067 --> 33:28.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Even so, officials continued
detaining and deporting
new Haitian arrivals.

33:28.833 --> 33:33.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But recent overcrowding
in detention centers have
led officials to allow
some Haitian migrants

33:34.567 --> 33:36.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
to enter the U.S.

33:36.733 --> 33:41.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Among the Haitians who managed
to cross into the U.S. before
the policy changes is Sandra

33:41.367 --> 33:45.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Alexandre, whose baby
was born hours after
she crossed the border.

33:45.667 --> 33:50.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The baby's father, Volcy
(ph), missed the birth and
still hasn't met his daughter.

33:52.633 --> 33:55.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He was supposed to cross a
few days after Sandra, right
when the policy shifted.

33:55.633 --> 33:59.400 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
When he crossed, he was
placed in an immigration
detention center.

33:59.400 --> 34:01.533 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He still hasn't been released.

34:01.533 --> 34:04.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SANDRA ALEXANDRE, HAITIAN
MIGRANT (through translator):
It's very difficult for me and

34:04.500 --> 34:06.767 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
for the baby.

34:06.767 --> 34:11.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I don't know when he's
going to come here.

34:13.967 --> 34:18.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GUERRERO: Alexandre says she
wishes she'd known the policy
was going to change before

34:18.433 --> 34:22.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
making the dangerous trek
through Latin America
with her fiance, while
she was nine months

34:22.933 --> 34:24.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
pregnant.

34:24.033 --> 34:26.100 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Many times she almost gave up.

34:26.100 --> 34:31.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ALEXANDRE: I was like, "it's
too difficult, I won't make
it," but Volcy said, "Yes, you

34:32.667 --> 34:34.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
can make it.

34:34.333 --> 34:36.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Little by little, but
you're going to make it.

34:36.567 --> 34:38.267 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Be brave."

34:38.267 --> 34:42.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
GUERRERO: She says she
can't go back to Haiti.

34:42.000 --> 34:44.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
ALEXANDRE: In Haiti,
life is very difficult.

34:44.733 --> 34:47.333 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Very, very, very difficult.

34:47.333 --> 34:49.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's also very dangerous.

34:49.933 --> 34:53.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GUERRERO: In the meantime,
Tijuana residents are
responding to Haitians
with unusual hospitality.

34:56.167 --> 35:01.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
All day, they stop by the
migrant shelters where Haitians
congregate, giving away clothes,

35:03.067 --> 35:08.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
dropping off snacks like
sandwiches and sports drinks,
even preparing full meals.

35:08.067 --> 35:12.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JANETH AGUILAR, TIJUANA
RESIDENT (through translator):
We come every day with them.

35:12.167 --> 35:13.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We bring them candy, food.

35:13.633 --> 35:15.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We're with them a little while.

35:15.633 --> 35:18.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Yesterday, they braided
my whole head of hair.

35:18.800 --> 35:23.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GUERRERO: She remembers when
she first saw the large crowds
of Haitians on the streets.

35:23.667 --> 35:28.667 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It was an unusual sight
-- only about 1 percent of
Mexico's population is black.

35:30.067 --> 35:33.100 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Aguilar went online to find
out what was happening.

35:33.100 --> 35:37.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
She learned that the migrants
were coming from countries
with political and economic

35:37.033 --> 35:39.400 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
crises, and she wanted to help.

35:39.400 --> 35:41.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
AGUILAR: We come to give
them a happy moment.

35:41.967 --> 35:46.967 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Since they lack everything,
we want to make sure
they don't lack a smile.

35:48.900 --> 35:52.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GUERRERO: The streets of Tijuana
have long been filled with
migrants heading to the U.S.,

35:52.833 --> 35:57.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
as well as the deported
-- mostly from southern
Mexico and Central America.

35:57.733 --> 36:02.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Those migrants are often
shunned by the locals, forced to
live out of sight, in sewers.

36:02.300 --> 36:07.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
When Tijuana residents recently
set up a table on the street,
offering fried chicken, rice

36:08.767 --> 36:11.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and beans to the Haitians, a
Mexican migrant got in line.

36:11.000 --> 36:16.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Jorge Cruz, a Tijuana taxi
driver who brought the chicken,
was not happy about that.

36:18.500 --> 36:20.467 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JORGE CRUZ, TIJUANA DRIVER
(through translator): I
told him, "You're Mexican,
what do you lack?"

36:20.467 --> 36:25.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GUERRERO: Despite the warm
welcome in Mexico, the Haitians
are intent on making it into

36:25.300 --> 36:27.300 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
the U.S.

36:27.300 --> 36:30.067 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
UNIDENTIFIED MALE (through
translator): I have
faith in Christ, in God.

36:30.067 --> 36:32.000 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
God is always helping me.

36:32.000 --> 36:35.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
GUERRERO: He knows he might
be placed in a detention
center and deported.

36:35.267 --> 36:39.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But that's not going to stop
him from trying, and hoping.

36:39.200 --> 36:44.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour", I'm Jean
Guerrero in Tijuana, Mexico.

36:46.733 --> 36:51.500 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
