36:51.500 --> 36:56.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: And to the analysis
of Shields and Brooks.

36:56.133 --> 37:00.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That is syndicated columnist
Mark Shields and "New York
Times" columnist David Brooks.

37:00.833 --> 37:02.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Gentlemen, welcome.

37:02.900 --> 37:07.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So let's start out talking
about two major foreign policy
waves, I guess you could say,

37:08.767 --> 37:10.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
that Donald Trump is
making today, David.

37:10.867 --> 37:15.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He directly intervened with
the White House as they were
deciding how to handle this U.N.

37:15.400 --> 37:16.867 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
resolution on Israel.

37:16.867 --> 37:20.000 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
There is now an open rift
with President Obama.

37:20.000 --> 37:23.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is different, isn't
it, from the way we see a
transition normally work?

37:23.867 --> 37:27.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DAVID BROOKS, NEW YORK
TIMES COLUMNIST: Certainly,
the country can't have
two presidents at once,

37:27.767 --> 37:30.933 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
