to hang back if you're
the president-elect
and wait for your

37:30.933 --> 37:33.067 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
time in office.

37:33.067 --> 37:35.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Trump is not a
hang-back kind of guy.

37:35.600 --> 37:40.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he has shifted --- President
Obama has shifted American
policy in a much more critical

37:42.200 --> 37:45.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
way in Israel with the
settlements than the
previous presidents.

37:45.033 --> 37:48.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But we're about to
get a head-snapping
shift the other way.

37:48.300 --> 37:52.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
President-elect Trump's
ambassador to Israel is further
to the right than almost anyone

37:52.800 --> 37:57.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in Israel, further to the right
than Bibi Netanyahu on the
settlements, and almost opposes

37:58.867 --> 38:00.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
the two-state
solution, doesn't he?

38:00.967 --> 38:04.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, we are about to see a
tremendous shift in American
policy toward the Middle East.

38:05.533 --> 38:07.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
WOODRUFF: How do
you see this, Mark?

38:07.567 --> 38:10.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Are there consequences of
this or is this going to be
something we look back on and

38:10.233 --> 38:12.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
say, well, that's what happened?

38:12.233 --> 38:14.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
MARK SHIELDS, SYNDICATED
COLUMNIST: No, I mean, I think
Donald Trump is sui generis.

38:14.133 --> 38:18.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I mean, he is acting by
president or tradition.

38:18.133 --> 38:23.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's acting as Donald Trump
has throughout his entire
public career of, what, a year

38:25.533 --> 38:30.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and a half, and that is to be
impulsive, be spontaneous, keep
his opponents or adversaries

38:32.033 --> 38:34.100 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
off balance.

38:34.100 --> 38:35.567 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
That's his approach.

38:35.567 --> 38:40.233 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He is not into nuance,
that is not his strength.

38:40.233 --> 38:45.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And the president said this
week, he's entitled to his own
policies and but just hope that

38:46.567 --> 38:48.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
it's deliberate and thoughtful.

38:48.933 --> 38:51.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And this strikes
me as anything but.

38:51.100 --> 38:55.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Well, in addition to
Israel, what we were sitting
here talking about nuclear

38:55.367 --> 39:00.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
policy because Donald Trump
tweeted, as far as we can tell,
out of the blue yesterday,

39:00.200 --> 39:03.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
David, that the United
States needs to beef
up its nuclear arsenal.

39:03.833 --> 39:08.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He did an interview with Mika
Brzezinski of NBC this morning
and I'm just reading the

39:10.133 --> 39:12.200 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
quote here.

39:12.200 --> 39:16.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He said, "Let it be an arms
race, we will outmatch them
at every pass and outlast them

39:18.933 --> 39:19.933 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
all."

39:19.933 --> 39:22.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, what does this say?

39:22.000 --> 39:24.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
BROOKS: Yes, one of the things
I think about with Donald Trump
is what are his words actually

39:24.633 --> 39:26.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
attached to?

39:26.633 --> 39:30.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
With a normal president like
President Obama, he says a word,
and that's because there has

39:30.100 --> 39:33.367 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
been some thought that he's
done and there had been
policy papers and there's been

39:33.367 --> 39:37.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
aides and there's been
advisors and then there is a
connection to an actual set of

39:37.233 --> 39:38.700 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
policies.

39:38.700 --> 39:41.600 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And so, the words like have
roots into actual stuff.

39:41.600 --> 39:44.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
With Trump, I'm not sure
the words have roots.

39:44.233 --> 39:48.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
They are emanations
of his psyche, but has
he thought it through?

39:48.333 --> 39:50.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Is there an argument, is
there a policy implication?

39:50.133 --> 39:53.767 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Even in this nuclear
thing, he says we should
be stronger and expand.

39:53.767 --> 39:55.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What does that mean?

39:55.033 --> 39:57.067 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
So, what is concrete
in what he's saying?

39:57.067 --> 40:01.467 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I think as we interpret him
and frankly as the world learns
to interpret Donald Trump,

40:01.467 --> 40:06.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
are these just words that are
enigmatic things floating on
air or are they actually shifts

40:06.133 --> 40:11.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
in policy and will they
change moment by moment,
day by day without any
underlying connection

40:12.233 --> 40:13.133 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to the actual stuff
of governance?

40:13.133 --> 40:14.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I don't know.

40:14.600 --> 40:17.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
WOODRUFF: Mark, we're talking
about nuclear arms policy.

40:17.200 --> 40:21.867 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This is something that in the
past, it was something that
people spent time thinking

40:21.867 --> 40:23.967 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
about before
statements were made.

40:23.967 --> 40:28.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You know, you said a minute
ago, you think he's keeping
everybody off balance.

40:28.233 --> 40:29.433 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Is this a deliberate strategy?

40:29.433 --> 40:31.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
SHIELDS: Well, I think
that's part of it.

40:31.300 --> 40:36.000 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The points David make
I think really deserve
reflection and consideration.

40:36.000 --> 40:41.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I think Donald Trump,
we have to understand,
has not had experiences
like any other president

40:41.933 --> 40:43.467 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
we've ever had.

40:43.467 --> 40:46.567 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He's never been accountable
to anybody, save Donald Trump.

40:46.567 --> 40:49.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
I mean, he has no investors.

40:49.033 --> 40:54.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He has -- he has debtors,
but he doesn't have
a board of directors.

40:55.467 --> 40:59.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He doesn't have a corporate
structure he's had to answer to.

40:59.433 --> 41:02.867 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So he's been able to kind
of wing it at every stage.

41:02.867 --> 41:07.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
I just don't think he
understands -- the point
David was making is
when a president makes

41:07.700 --> 41:12.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a statement, Judy, it is studied
around the world, the nuance
and was there an emphasis

41:15.167 --> 41:18.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
here, and what was
in the last statement
that's missing -- perhaps
overly done, maybe overly

41:18.400 --> 41:20.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
analyzed.

41:20.900 --> 41:24.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But because the president's
words are pretentious,
they really carry with
them enormous significance

41:26.833 --> 41:31.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and are usually reflective
of great consideration
and even arguments
within that one side is

41:32.967 --> 41:36.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
wanted, one particular paragraph
or sentence, while the other
said, no, that shouldn't be

41:36.700 --> 41:38.600 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in there.

41:38.600 --> 41:42.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I just think that Trump
-- he has not made the
transition, it seems to me, from

41:44.233 --> 41:47.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
candidate to even
president in waiting.

41:47.933 --> 41:49.933 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
He has been a sore winner.

41:49.933 --> 41:54.933 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
He continues to in his rallies
to berate Hillary Clinton.

41:56.867 --> 42:01.267 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That sense of gracious,
generosity or larger vision
has eluded him so far.

42:03.233 --> 42:06.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WOODRUFF: But, David, some --
not but -- and some people,
David, have looked at what he's

42:06.233 --> 42:09.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
doing and they said, this is
really part of a strategy.

42:09.133 --> 42:12.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Keep people off balance,
keep them guessing about
what you're going to do.

42:12.667 --> 42:14.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
BROOKS: I think that's
a rationalization for
just the way he is.

42:14.900 --> 42:17.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But it does have the effect
of keeping people off balance.

42:17.433 --> 42:19.733 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I'm not sure that's
necessarily a good thing.

42:19.733 --> 42:24.167 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And to bring us back to the
nuclear thing, keeping people
off balance with nuclear weapons

42:24.167 --> 42:25.733 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
is not a good thing at all.

42:25.733 --> 42:28.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
SHIELDS: No.

42:28.300 --> 42:31.633 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BROOKS: And -- so I
would say, given, as Mark
describes, sort of -- he's
not part of a process.

42:31.633 --> 42:34.767 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so, I think there
are two things that could
happen as a result of this.

